The paper focuses on motion planning for automated vehicles, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The use of mixed-integer quadratic optimization and neural networks also suggests a strong presence of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the need for safe and efficient driving in complicated traffic conditions, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the numerical simulations mentioned in the paper may involve computer vision techniques for analyzing traffic scenarios (cs.CV).
